STATE of Louisiana
v.
Ontrell WASHINGTON No. 2018-KD-0742 Supreme Court of Louisiana. August 31, 2018

ON SUPERVISORY WRIT TO THE CRIMINAL DISTRICT COURT, FOR THE PARISH OF ORLEANS

CRICHTON, J., would grant and assigns reasons:

I would grant the State's writ application to vacate the trial court's ruling and reinstate the defendant's conviction and sentence.

WEIMER, J., would grant and docket.

CLARK, J., would grant and docket.

CRICHTON, J., would grant and assigns reasons.
